trans-unit.source: Represents a field of an <xref href="System.Web.UI.MobileControls.ObjectList"></xref> ASP.NET mobile control.
trans-unit.target: 代表的欄位<xref href="System.Web.UI.MobileControls.ObjectList"> </xref> ASP.NET 行動控制項。

trans-unit.source: This class cannot be inherited.
trans-unit.target: 這個類別無法被繼承。

trans-unit.source: For information about how to develop ASP.NET mobile applications, see the [www.asp.net/mobile](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=182900) Web site.

trans-unit.source: A field is of type ObjectListField.
trans-unit.target: 欄位是 ObjectListField 型別。

trans-unit.source: When you want to display multiple fields, you can specify multiple fields for each item in an object list.
trans-unit.target: 當您想要顯示多個欄位時，您可以指定多個欄位，每個項目中的物件清單。

trans-unit.source: To create a field within the declaration of an <xref:System.Web.UI.MobileControls.ObjectList>, you declare an ObjectListField as a `<Field>` element.
trans-unit.target: 若要建立的宣告中的欄位<xref:System.Web.UI.MobileControls.ObjectList>，宣告為 ObjectListField`<Field>`項目。</xref:System.Web.UI.MobileControls.ObjectList>

trans-unit.source: Each field is associated with a property name.
trans-unit.target: 每個欄位是相關聯的屬性名稱。

trans-unit.source: When a list item is bound to a data object, each field is bound to the corresponding property of the object.
trans-unit.target: 當清單項目已繫結至資料物件時，每個欄位都繫結物件的對應屬性。

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Web.UI.MobileControls.ObjectList> provides three ways to define a field: - Declaratively, by using `<Field>` child elements within the object list - Programmatically, by constructing ObjectListField objects and adding them to the Fields member collection of the control - Automatically, by setting the <xref:System.Web.UI.MobileControls.ObjectList.AutoGenerateFields%2A> property to `true`.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Web.UI.MobileControls.ObjectList>提供三種方式來定義欄位︰︰ 以宣告方式，是藉由使用`<Field>`子項目內的物件清單-以程式設計的方式，透過建構 ObjectListField 物件，並將它們加入至控制項的欄位成員集合-自動執行，藉由設定<xref:System.Web.UI.MobileControls.ObjectList.AutoGenerateFields%2A>屬性`true`。</xref:System.Web.UI.MobileControls.ObjectList.AutoGenerateFields%2A> </xref:System.Web.UI.MobileControls.ObjectList>
